<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idd39983d9-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370" identifier="/us/usc/t11/s784"><num value="784">§ 784.</num><heading> Right to be heard</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Board or a Federal reserve bank (in the case of a clearing bank that is a member of that bank) may raise and may appear and be heard on any issue in a case under this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idd39983da-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/106/554/s1/a/5/tI/s112/c/5/B">Pub. L. 106–554, § 1(a)(5) [title I, § 112(c)(5)(B)]</ref>, <date date="2000-12-21">Dec. 21, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/2763">114 Stat. 2763</ref>, 2763A–395.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
